<br>
Instead, the way I believe all epic mobs should be is you have to get a rare drop off a common mob. Then you take that rare drop and trigger the epic spawn (which then spawns immediately). At worst this means you have to wait 12 hours to spawn him again. Sure, that means you will still be farming and camping, but you will be able to be doing something while camping plus one person couldn't dominate the entire spawn for days on end (theorectically anyway). Now, this wouldn't stop guilds from monopolizing spawns, etc, but that would be far less common than the crap that goes on now.<br>
<br>
Also, the fact that certain mobs drop an epic item for more than one class is stupid too. Now, not only are you competing with people from your own class you're having the same problem with other peoples too.<br>
<br>
/sigh. Ok, enough pissing and moaning about epics. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=charr>Charr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/02 9:36:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1094.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Disputes</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also, the fact that certain mobs drop an epic item for more than one class is stupid too. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
